            "id": "https://www.grahamrust.me/blog/3d-printed-vr-ball-3/index.html",
            "url": "https://www.grahamrust.me/blog/3d-printed-vr-ball-3/index.html",
            "title": "3D Printed VR Ball",
            "summary": "Made with Autodesk Maya/Fusion and brought into Unreal Engine. Download the 3D model now to have a ball in VR! Printed with Anycubic Photon S 3D printer Lego figure for scale. He loves his custom 1:10 scale Tundra Trackers Old prototypes. The first version (white)&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<div class=\"align-center\">Made with Autodesk Maya/Fusion and brought into Unreal Engine. Download the <a href=\"https://grabcad.com/library/vr-ball-for-tundra-tracker-1\">3D model</a> now to have a ball in VR!</div>\n<div class=\"post__video\"><div class=\"post__iframe\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"696\" height=\"389\" style=\"width: 696px; height: 389px;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/tfgQtob6GWI\" title=\"Video\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div></div>\n<p class=\"align-center\"><a href=\"https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/vrball.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/vrball.jpg\" alt=\"\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/vrball-xs.jpg 640w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/vrball-sm.jpg 768w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/vrball-md.jpg 1024w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/vrball-lg.jpg 1366w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/vrball-xl.jpg 1600w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/vrball-2xl.jpg 1920w\"></a></p>\n<p class=\"align-center\">Printed with Anycubic Photon S 3D printer</p>\n<p class=\"align-center\"><a href=\"https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/halfvrball.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/halfvrball.jpg\" alt=\"\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/halfvrball-xs.jpg 640w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/halfvrball-sm.jpg 768w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/halfvrball-md.jpg 1024w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/halfvrball-lg.jpg 1366w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/halfvrball-xl.jpg 1600w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/halfvrball-2xl.jpg 1920w\"></a></p>\n<p class=\"align-center\">Lego figure for scale. He loves his custom 1:10 scale Tundra Trackers</p>\n<p class=\"align-center\"><a href=\"https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/v1v2vrball.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/v1v2vrball.jpg\" alt=\"\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/v1v2vrball-xs.jpg 640w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/v1v2vrball-sm.jpg 768w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/v1v2vrball-md.jpg 1024w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/v1v2vrball-lg.jpg 1366w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/v1v2vrball-xl.jpg 1600w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/v1v2vrball-2xl.jpg 1920w\"></a></p>\n<p class=\"align-center\">Old prototypes. The first version (white) was too thick and covered the sensors too much. The 2nd version was too thin. The third was just right</p>\n<p class=\"align-center\"><a href=\"https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/fov.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/fov.png\" alt=\"\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/fov-xs.png 640w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/fov-sm.png 768w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/fov-md.png 1024w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/fov-lg.png 1366w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/fov-xl.png 1600w ,https://www.grahamrust.me/media/posts/10/responsive/fov-2xl.png 1920w\"></a></p>\n<p class=\"align-center\"><strong>Left:</strong> Valve released 3D models showing the area the tracking sensors cannot see, for creating accessories that don't interfere with tracking</p>\n<p class=\"align-center\"><strong>Right:</strong> I created the same type of model for the Tundra Tracker using Autodesk Fusion. Download <a href=\"https://grabcad.com/library/sensor-inclusion-zone-model-for-tundra-tracker-1\">here</a>. The tracker 3D model was created by Tundra</p>",
